================================================================
Why AGPL-3.0-or-later?
================================================================

The intent is to keep this codebase open. Anyone can self-host,
modify, or fork. But anyone running a hosted service derived from
this code must publish their modifications. That is the
core difference from a permissive license like Apache-2.0 or MIT,
and it's deliberate: hosted SaaS reviewers (CodeRabbit, Greptile,
etc.) demonstrated that a permissive license would let a fork-and-
close-source story repeat itself for Forgejo.
